author: Mark Woodley
title: North Texas fires Dan McCarney
text:
North Texas fires Dan McCarney Posted: Denton, Texas (KWWL) - 
After 5 seasons as the school's head football coach, Dan McCarney has been fired at North Texas 
The dismissal comes after the Mean Green lost 66-7 against Portland State out of the NCAA's FCS division. McCarney, who led Iowa State's program until 2006, went 22-32 at North Texas. His best season came in 2013 when his team went 9-4 and won the Heart of Dallas Bowl.
